    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER AND AUXILIARY GAUGE SWITCH PACK - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        DIGITAL DISPLAY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x0825417" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>DIGITAL DISPLAY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Circuit Function</title>
            <para>The EGC has an integral liquid crystal display (LCD).</para>
            <para>The three lines of the digital display provide a PRNDL display, a numeric display, and a line to
                indicate the mode of the display.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Diagnostics</title>
            <para>Problems with the digital display can be caused by loose connections between the display and the
                circuit board, a failed display or a failed EGC circuit board.
            </para>
            <table id="t0825458" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Digital Display Preliminary Check</title>
                <tgroup cols="6" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.53in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.62in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="1.20in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="1.14in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.51in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
